                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>
                              <objectType>Wall</objectType> of stage building.  The blocks were left rough, with a smooth outline along the edges.</p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>Cut on some smoothed patches, some of them at least prepared to offer guidelines for the architects planning the Theatre façade. a above, b below and to the south, c below b, d between a and b.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>a. Large letters, scratched and irregular, with cursive alpha and omega, av. <height unit="metre">0.08</height>. b; tiny letters <height unit="metre">0.01</height>. c: Below b. Large letters, irregular, av. <height unit="metre">0.08</height>. d: very large letters in red paint, <height unit="metre">0.17-0.19</height>.</handNote>
